<Author>JoshNL
<Content>Avoid this hotel Guys, I'm Dutch and know Dutch/Amsterdam standard hotels/prices... This hotel (at least the room they gave us) was way below standard. The room was right on the stairway in front of the lift, very noisy.. we're not offended by noise though but would bother the noise-sensitives. The room was dirty, damp, white TL lights, very small, beds overused, soft and uncomfartable, bed linen very dirty, full of stains and holes and stinking (we slept with our clothes on, on a july night just to avoid skin contact with the bed linen), bathroom out-of-date from the 80's standard white tile walls and the most annoying was the day after, all the itch and bite spots from the bugs... Paid 90 Euros per night per room, and believe me, there are much much better places to stay even cheaper.. The room size is small, but if that was the only problem i wouldn't mind at all... PS: We booked for two nights but left after the first night simply because we couldn't stay there any minute longer, had no refunds, and booked another hotel for the second night, very close, cleaner and even a few euros cheaper.... I would never ever ever go back and i'd think twice if i were you before booking here... 
