<Author>mirvera
<Content>Just Perfect just perfect, i've spent in this hotel 4 nights and it couldn't have been better, at the beginning i wasn't sure about my decision but then again i just needed a clean, small room to spend a few days in the last free city of planet earth, i wasn't with family or girlfriend so i did not have much to risk. During these 4 days i had the chance to meet the guys who run the place, and they were all very friendly and easygoing, expecially Mario, a great guy who was always willing to help. The rooms are small, no doubt about it, but i can assure that they're clean and confortable, i even had a small plasma tv with cable channell, and considering that it's a budget hotel, i'd say it's incredible.I had a room in the back side of the building so the view from the room was very poor (and i've been told that from Mario when i arrived, so he's been honest) but i could sleep peacefully like a baby without noise; there are also room on the front side, and they have a great view on one of the main strip, but ovviously could be noisy...Never had breakfast so i don't really know, but nobody was complaining about it so i guess it was good.The hotel is 10min walking to anywhere so i never had to take a taxi and that helped a lot since taxi are incredible expensive in Amsterdam.To make a lontg story short, this is the best budget hotel i've ever been to and i would definately suggest it to every easygoing, well-natured person who wants to live Amsterdam as a friend of the city and not as a snob tourist.Thanks to Mario and to the staff 
