<Author>L0na
<Content>Great hotel!!! A friend and I were looking at the reviews on Hotel Rokin and as I'm quite the girly girl and will not tolerate bugs I was very dubious about booking after the reviews. I was told however by my male companion to just suck it up as it was getting quite late for booking and I was lucky he wasn't making me stay in a hostel with 20 people to a room!!! So we booked it and on arrival was just in shock at how nice the place is!! Coffee and minerals machine in the reception and big couches as part of the bar! Straight away we were given our key by a lovely receptionist and got such a nice welcome. Sure the room was small but it was warm (it was snowing when we were there!), had 2 single intact beds with crisp white sheets and clean pillows (the throw was a bit shabby but you wouldn't need it as it's warm in the rooms), a spotless bathroom with the usual soaps and shampoos etc in it! Only complaint I had was that there was no key to our safety deposit bow but it was no hassle to have the passports in a handbag as that's all we were planning on using it for!You could come and go 24 hrs as long as you left your key with reception. Nothing was ever taken from our luggage which included iPods, cameras, memory cards!Breakfast was your usual continental with everything as fresh and tasty as you liked and no complaints there! We didn't take advantage of the bar so can't say much about that!Overall the hotel is great and more you can ask for given the price is reasonable! If you're looking for spacy bedrooms however go elsewhere! Rooms are cosy but with plenty of space to move around and store your luggage!! Besides what else do you use a hotel room for except sleeping, showering and changing?! No problems with noise, bugs, leaks, mould or anything else!! I have it booked again for my next trip in the summer!! Totally central to everything and very easy to find!!Book this hotel as long as you're not in need of a massive room!! 
