<Author>Lang0ustine
<Content>Can't see what everyone is complaining about! Well, after booking this hotel, I had a look on tripadvisor.com to see how other people had rated their experiences at this hotel.  What insued was a mad frenzy of paranoia about bedbugs and fear that I had booked a horrible hotel.  Upon arrival I was encouraged by the friendly staff, who didn't fail to impress once, even at 3am when we arrived back at reception enquiring about how to get to the Amsterdam Arena for our following days outing, the staff were friendly and helpful even drawing us a map.  The rooms were quite small and yes the decor was slightly old fashioned but I was impressed with the modern and spotlessly clean bathrooms. None of the rooms had bed bugs, we had three rooms and 10 beds, not one had bed bugs, believe me, I checked thoroughly having watched countless videos and tutorials on how to spot them.  Breakfast was basic, but for the price of the hotel we hadn't exactly been expecting a sumptuous feast. The location was good, the shops on one side, ten minutes from the main clubbing and bar area and of course the infamous red light district on the other side, which is a must see for anyone. All in all, we had a great trip, with the hotel being an excellent HQ for us, I would recommend this hotel to any groups of 18-25 year olds who want a good location, comfortable beds and somewhere to wash. If you are looking for luxury then perhaps this hotel is not for you but anyone with any sense would instantly recognise that due to the price of staying here. 
