<Content>Go elsewhere! I visited Amsterdam with some friends last weekend and we had the misfortune of staying at the Hotel Cordial. There were 4 of us, 3 girls who shared a room and a male friend who had a room by himself. Both rooms were small and dingy. The girls' room stank of stale smoke on arrival (and the smell never really went away as if it had permeated the curtains and the carpet) and the view was non existant since it gave onto an alleyway and all we could see was the wall opposite. My male friend's room was hardly better because, although it gave onto the Rokin, it was very noisy due to the heavy works going on at the moment. The hotel is in dire need of a facelift as the whole place has a grubby feel to it which is very unpleasant. The staff are borderline rude and could hardly be called welcoming. You got the impression that they would rather be somewhere else (and who could blame them?!). The breakfast is OK but nothing special. Amsterdam is a fantastic city and I am sure there are many cheap-ish hotels available so my advice is to look elsewhere. I travel quite a bit and I find it really galling when hotels get away with poor service, like this one. 
