<Content>GREAT BUDGET HOTEL Just returned from a two night stay at hotel cordial, 3rd visit to amsterdam.Just 8 mins walk from central station in an ideal location, (apart from building works but its unavoidable in amsterdam at present, but with the window shut through day it bocks out most of the noise.Only 2 mins walk from dam square, lots of eating and drinking places surrounding, shopping on the doorstep and lots of attractions only walking distance.We were given the choice of 4 different double rooms on arrival, we choose 4th floor, our room was clean, and nicely presented,could do with a lick of paint but its ok. In the room was a hairdryer, tv with some english channels,a walldrobe, dressing table and a large mirror.The ensuite was very small with just a shower and toilet, which were kept very clean and 4 towels were provided.Our room was cleaned during our stay and bed made.Breakfast was traditional dutch was served in a cosy breakfast room,comprising of cereal, bread rolls, ham, salami,cheese and boiled eggs, all fresh and nicely presented. The waiter kept filling our cups with coffee or tea when we were empty.I havent got any bad views of hotel cordial,for a budget hotel i found it excellent value for money.I will be booking to stay again on my next visit to amsterdam. 
