<Content>Great location, but beware the Silent Assassins. Just returned from a weekend in Amsterdam and was pleasantly surprised with the Hotel Cordial.The location is great. 2 minutes walk from Dam Square (The Centre Point of Amsterdam) it is perfectly located for enjoying Amsterdam, bars and clubs and coffee shops are less that 10 minutes staggering time away. The main shopping street is located behind the hotel and the floating flower stalls are 5 minutes walk away. Central station is no more than 15 minutes walk.Our room was a decent size with good facilities and clean. If you are looking to spend more time in the room than in the city, then stay elsewhere, but as a base to explore and enjoy the fun of the city, it's great.There are extensive road works happening in front of the hotel but they were finished by 6pm and not on the Sunday that we were there. As a family hotel I would not recommend the Cordial, but for couples or travelling friends, its perfectly located, clean and adequate and if you say thank you to the receptionist in Dutch (Dank) they are easier to deal with.The Silent Assassins, by the way, are the cyclists who abound within the city. You watch out for trams and cars and next second find a bicycle charging towards you waiting for the last second to ring their bell. And there are another 20 bikes behind that one. Scary but it heightens your reflexes.All in all, the Cordial is a welcome tonic, great location, decent rooms and facilities, just don't buy coffee from the bar, it's expensive and you don't get much in a cup. 
